The City of Tshwane will respond to Rapid Transit workers’ demands next Wednesday. Silindelo Masikane, has been following this story. Courtesy of #DStv403 TSHWANE - The City of Tshwane will respond to Rapid Transit workers’ demands next Wednesday. They're demanding transport allowances. READ: Numsa March | TRT drivers march for travel allowances Workers say this is a basic condition of employment and they're angry the city is ignoring their rights. Numsa is representing workers who marched to the municipal offices at Tshwane House. Workers say their strike will continue until their demands are met.